-EC2 Instance/VM
==========================
-Create/Launch New Instance (server)
-Choose Instance Type 
-Enter Instance Number 
	-Network
	-Subnet
	-Public IP 
-Storage 
	-8 gb is default of linux 

-Tag  : keyname 
	
-Generate key:
	webserver_aug28.pem
-Server/Instance name : 
		webserver_aug28
save private key with new name

	


Public DNS (IPv4)
	ec2-52-23-241-113.compute-1.amazonaws.com

Install Putty Client:

url:
https://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/putty/


-Install putty client/connector
-Open the putty gen and load the download public key
-and then click on save and save private key on local drive
-Open putty client 


-Configure the putty client using
			ip address
			user
			auth key/private key

-Connect the server
-Linux Commands
==================
$pwd 	: show current path
$ll	: show long list of files and folder
$ls	: show short list
$mkdir dirname : create new folder/directory
$cd dirname    : change directory 
$cat > filename.txt   : create new file 
...enter content
ctrl+z		: to save file 


$cat filename.txt	            : show content of file

$cat filename.txt >> nefilename.txt : make new file from existing file 

$rm filename.txt	   : remove file 
$cp sourcefile destfile    : copy file from source to destination 
$mv sourcfile destlocation : move file from source to destination 
$cd .. : go one folder back
$cd ~  : go to root/parent directory 



			


